"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, I get the question all the time what do I think about RFK and its 700 million uh towards farming that's some uh that's better than what we have or whatever it is. I don't know. I don't look into it, uh it's not my world. I'm believe it or not, I really don't care. Uh it's I am trying to start something that's at the ground level, that's truly grassroots. Policy, I don't understand it, I've never really got it, and it doesn't really affect me. I mean, everyone will say, of course it affects you, and blah blah blah. I get that, okay. But what I'm focusing on is a personal return to the decay cycle and the cultivation of that decay cycle. Um that what I think we need to do is not grow food better off in some distant farm, have it shipped over here as better food. I think we have to personally, and when I say personally, as a community, we have to rededicate ourselves to cultivating the decay cycles to take these beneficial microbes that come from this decay cycle and reincorporate them into our lives. We need to make our own food personally, and we need to make our own compost personally. We need to do these things because we have alienated our systems, our biomes, from the world's biomes and from the microbes, and we've kind of sterilized ourselves in this whole process, and that's what we need to really work on. It's it's not about policy, it's not about what the government decides to do or who you vote for, it's about what you're doing in your backyard, it's about what you're doing in your community gardens. It's about putting your hands in living soil and cultivating that living soil and getting the bacterial transfer, the the lateral gene transfer of the DNA from the bacteria from the most basic forms of life all the way back towards you. And this is how we fix our health problems, and this is how we fix our our agricultural problems, and this is all the things that I think we need to do, and it doesn't have anything to do with policy or the subsidies or any of these things that are happening off in Washington or even at my state level or however it goes, we need to work at a personal level. We need to not think in terms of the grand picture and look at ourselves and what's happening to our health and how do we directly fix this. It has nothing to do with medicine or policy or big ag or big pharma or any of this stuff. It's how we interact with our environment. And that's that's my whole purpose is to convey that message. So when people are like, oh, what do you think about the newest policy? I'm like, I don't know. I don't I don't really follow it. You know, I'm trying to make a change in my personal life and then show others, you know, that how to maybe do this as well, if if I get it right. And it doesn't have anything to do with the big picture. It has everything to do with me and my small picture and my life and my personal existence. And so that's where I stand. Uh I don't know. I don't I don't I don't really know about any of this stuff. Anyway, just wanted to make a video that I'm politically ignorant and um probably gonna stay that way. Sorry, but thanks.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, I get the question all the time what do I think about RFK and its 700 million uh towards farming that's some uh that's better than what we have or whatever it is.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 10.48,\n      \"duration\": 10.16,\n      \"confidence\": 0.983,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.911\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.72,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.998\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n          \"end\": 0.96,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confide